<h2 id="summary-measure-reporting">Summary Measure Reporting</h2>

<p>When the results of a quality measure are completed for a population at the end of a measurement period, they are POSTed to the quality measure Receiverâ€™s FHIR Server. The report may only consist of the Summary MeasureReport in which case it is POSTed to the MeasureReport endpoint.  If there are other referenced resources all the resources are bundled together as a set of <code class="highlighter-rouge">POST</code> interactions and sent as a single <a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/http.html#transaction">transaction</a> interaction using the Standard FHIR API. Multiple summary results can be sent in a single FHIR Bundle as described <a href="indv-reporting.html#individual-measure-reporting">here</a>.  (Note that if the Bundle consist of only Summary MeasureReports, then a <a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/bundle.html#collection">collection</a> bundle is used.)</p>

<p>Posting a Summary Measure Report is typically a one time event, although there may be a need to amend or update a report or to report periodically based on the reporting program.  The FHIR transaction bundle used in the reporting scenarios SHALL contains only the new and updated DEQM and QI Core Profiles since the last transaction or those that need to be deleted. (<code class="highlighter-rouge">Bundle.request.method</code> = POST, PUT, or DELETE).</p>

